@page "/faq"

<PageTitle>FAQ – Rota</PageTitle>

<div class="faq-wrapper">
    <div class="faq-header">
        <h2 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="faq-subtitle">Everything you need to know about using Rota.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <h5 class="faq-section-title">📅 Calendar &amp; Schedules</h5>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I view my schedule?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Log in and click <strong>Schedules</strong> in the navigation menu. You can switch between the week and month views using the buttons at the top of the calendar.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I navigate between months or weeks?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Use the <strong>‹</strong> and <strong>›</strong> buttons to move backward or forward. Click <strong>Today</strong> to jump back to the current date.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <h5 class="faq-section-title">🕐 Shifts</h5>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I add a shift?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Click any day on the calendar to open the day view, then click <strong>+ Shift</strong>. Fill in the start time, end time, worker type, and any notes, then click <strong>Create Shift</strong>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Can I create a recurring shift?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Yes. When adding a shift, choose a <strong>Repeat</strong> option — Daily, Work week (Mon–Fri), or Weekends only — and Rota will create one shift for every matching day in that month.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I edit or delete a shift?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Click a shift card anywhere on the calendar to open the edit form. Change any fields and click <strong>Save Changes</strong>, or click <strong>Delete</strong> to remove it.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <h5 class="faq-section-title">🔔 Reminders</h5>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I add a reminder?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Click a day on the calendar and then click <strong>+ Reminder</strong>. Enter a title, pick a time and colour, add optional notes, and click <strong>Save</strong>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">What do the reminder colours mean?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Colours are purely for your own organisation — use them however you like, for example red for urgent items and green for completed tasks.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I edit or delete a reminder?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Click a reminder on the calendar or in the day detail view to open it for editing. You can update any field or click <strong>Delete</strong> to remove it.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <h5 class="faq-section-title">🔐 Account</h5>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How long does my login session last?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Your session lasts <strong>8 hours</strong> from the time you log in. After that you will be asked to log in again.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">How do I log out?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">Click the <strong>Logout</strong> link in the top-right corner of any page.</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
